  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '<size=64><b>Notifications and Focused Learning</b></size>


    Doering
    and Barke''s 2022 experiment tested how smartphone alerts affect learning in
    a short lecture. University students watched the same material while either
    receiving push notifications, using a phone game without alerts, or studying
    without the game.


    Quiz results showed the clearest cost in the notification
    condition. Even brief alerts pulled attention away from the lecture and lowered
    recall, while students often underestimated the damage.


    The practical lesson
    is simple: during study, silence push notifications or use focus mode. Protecting
    attention keeps the thread of explanation intact long enough for learning to
    settle.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
